  "note": "Codified from the City of Leander Code of Ordinances, Chapter 14 (Zoning), Exhibit A Zoning Ordinance, Article VI (Site Standards) Section 6 (Setbacks) — Supplement 4 Update 1, codified through Ordinance No. 25-078-00 enacted December 18, 2025 (Municode ProductID 12187, job Id 487773). Source is Municode; the setback values cite Article VI Sec. 6, the single-family building/structure setback table. MODELING NOTES: (1) The Leander setback table columns are Front, Side, Street Side, Rear. 'Street Side' is codified as side_corner_ft (the corner/street-facing side). (2) The Leander zoning ordinance (a form-based/SmartCode-style code) states NO simple per-district maximum building height in feet and NO per-district lot-coverage or impervious-cover cap in the dimensional/setback or lot-size-summary sections; max_height_ft, max_lot_coverage_pct, and max_impervious_pct are therefore all not_specified and carry 100 as non-binding stand-ins (the envelope draw uses setbacks, not these fields). (3) SFC/SFL side is stated \"5' or 0' & 10'\" (attached / zero-lot-line option); the conventional 5 ft interior side is codified and flagged. SFT side is stated \"0 or 10'\" (attached / detached option); the attached 0 is codified as the base with the alternative flagged. (4) Districts with a note-marked garage/ROW exception (front value carries '*', min 18' to ROW for the garage) retain the table's stated front building setback. (5) Nonresidential/multifamily districts (NR/MF/LO/LC/GC/HC/HI) use a Max-Front + Min-Front + Min-Side + Street-Side + Min-Rear format; the Min values are codified where present, Max-Front is not a setback minimum and is excluded. LO and LC share a table row; codified identically.",
